Tuesday September 17th 2013 2:38 pm -04:00,The square brackets indicate a list. The song is one element of the list. So when you call the function you use the playlist name as the first parameter and the song name as the second parameter. If you call your list song_list and one of the songs is songA then the function call is cap_song_repetition(song_list songA). Then the code should change the list to have a maximum of three instances of songA. , Resolved,0
